This paper deals with the task of style transfer for text, which is a common topic in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes new architectures that outperform state of the art, which suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper mentions sentiment transfer, which is a common task in NLP, but also has applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
